==English==

===Adjective===
'''big old'''

#Emphatically or impressively [[big]]; [[really]] big.  

====Usage notes====
U.S. slang, esp. Southern dialects.  This phrase has no comparative or superlative forms.  Contrary to what is shown above (can't turn it off), '''big old''' is never used with '''more''' or '''most'''.

====Derived terms====
'''big ole'''

Same meaning.  (Almost exclusively Southern U.S.)

